timeline
    title Output Patterns: Sleep() Scenarios
    
    section Problem 4: Sleep After Print
        150ms: T1: a
        200ms: T2: X
        250ms: T3: +
        300ms: T4: .
        500ms: T1: a (awake)
        550ms: T2: X (awake)
        600ms: T3: + (awake)
        650ms: T4: . (awake)
        note: Very even round-robin pattern
        note: One character per thread per cycle
        note: Much longer total time (~100 seconds)
    
    section Problem 5: Sleep After Thread Creation
        0ms: T1 created, starts
        0-100ms: a a a a a (lots of 'a')
        500ms: T2 created, starts
        500ms: a X a X a (interleaving begins)
        1000ms: T3 created, starts
        1000ms: X + a X + a (more interleaving)
        1500ms: T4 created, starts
        1500ms: + . X a + . (full concurrency)
        note: Sequential start, then concurrent
        note: First 200 chars mostly 'a'
        note: Total time ~20 seconds
